I have moved to SEQUENCE_CHECKER.

Chrome has threads and sequences. See https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src/+/main/docs/threading_and_tasks.md#prefer-sequences-to-physical-threads for more details. You probably fine with a SEQEUNCE_CHECKER if you don’t have specific threading constraints.

Also note that Mojo already guarantees that IPCs will be dispatched to the sequence on which the Receiver was bound. (That is not to say that Receiver is thread/sequence-safe, it can only be called into from a single sequence).
